          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "PBh6w",
          "name": "problemSectionH",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "height": 1060,
          "fill": "#0A0A0B",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 22,
          "padding": 72,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "FPCMK",
              "name": "eyebrowP",
              "fill": "#4DD7C8",
              "content": "THE PROBLEM",
              "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "GJgFN",
              "name": "problemTitleH",
              "fill": "#F7F8FA",
              "content": "Critical energy workflows still rely\non records that are hard to trust.\nThat breaks operations.",
              "fontFamily": "Manrope",
              "fontSize": 58,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "w22Lq",
              "name": "problemBodyH",
              "fill": "#96A0AD",
              "content": "The issue is bigger than billing. Once telemetry becomes operationally\nor financially important, teams need deterministic records, audit trails,\nand evidence they can defend.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Manrope",
              "fontSize": 18,
              "fontWeight": "500"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "HVO9X",
              "name": "problemRowA",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 560,
              "gap": 28,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "XDnhe",
                  "name": "problemEntropyA",
                  "width": 280,
                  "height": 280,
                  "fill": "#12161D"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "Bh2wM",
                  "name": "problemCardsA",
                  "width": 900,
                  "height": 420,
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 14,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "aZGab",
                      "name": "problemCard1A",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "height": 150,
                      "fill": "#12161D",
                      "padding": 18,
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "3ah3W",
                          "name": "problemCard1TextA",
                          "fill": "#FF7B66",
                          "content": "01  Telemetry changes meaning as it moves\n\nField data passes through gateways, spreadsheets, operators, and settlement teams. By the time it matters, nobody can independently prove the original record.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.5,
                          "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                          "fontSize": 16,
                          "fontWeight": "600"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "CqsH1",
                      "name": "problemCard2A",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "height": 150,
                      "fill": "#12161D",
                      "padding": 18,
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "sELKd",
                          "name": "problemCard2TextA",
                          "fill": "#FF7B66",
                          "content": "02  Reconciliation takes too long\n\nEnergy operations still spend days or weeks reconciling mismatches across sites, systems, and counterparties. The delay is operationally expensive and commercially risky.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.5,
                          "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                          "fontSize": 16,
                          "fontWeight": "600"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "zAY8P",
                      "name": "problemCard3A",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "height": 150,
                      "fill": "#12161D",
                      "padding": 18,
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "M9xx8",
                          "name": "problemCard3TextA",
                          "fill": "#FF7B66",
                          "content": "03  Disputes start with weak evidence\n\nWhen a tariff, session, or operational dispute happens, the conversation often falls back to screenshots and spreadsheets instead of tamper-evident proof.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.5,
                          "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                          "fontSize": 16,
                          "fontWeight": "600"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "oA6XX",
          "name": "solutionSectionH",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "height": 1400,
          "fill": "#EEF2F6",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 22,
          "padding": 72,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "dzHi0",
              "name": "eyebrowS",
              "fill": "#5A6777",
              "content": "THE SOLUTION",
              "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "zvfml",
              "name": "solutionTitleH",
              "fill": "#101419",
              "content": "Turn raw telemetry into evidence\nthat survives audits, disputes,\nand handoffs.",
              "fontFamily": "Manrope",
              "fontSize": 58,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "XPWxf",
              "name": "solutionBodyH",
              "fill": "#556273",
              "content": "JouleBridge starts at the edge. Data is captured close to the source,\nnormalized into deterministic records, wrapped with verification metadata,\nand checked by policy before it persists.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Manrope",
              "fontSize": 18,
              "fontWeight": "500"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "oMLgP",
              "name": "solutionButtonA",
              "fill": "#101419",
              "content": "HOW IT WORKS",
              "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "11b01",
              "name": "solutionFlowA",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 340,
              "fill": "#FFFFFF"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "65CKu",
              "name": "solutionCardsA",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 440,
              "gap": 18,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "3YaRX",
                  "name": "solutionCard1A",
                  "width": 400,
                  "height": 300,
                  "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                  "padding": 20,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "hHA4V",
                      "name": "solutionCard1TextA",
                      "fill": "#101419",
                      "content": "01  DETERMINISTIC CAPTURE\n\nJouleBridge starts at the edge.\nData is captured close to the source\nand normalized into deterministic\nrecords before the evidence\ntrail begins.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.5,
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "busmc",
                  "name": "solutionCard2A",
                  "width": 400,
                  "height": 320,
                  "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                  "padding": 20,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "P1FxV",
                      "name": "solutionCard2TextA",
                      "fill": "#101419",
                      "content": "02  VERIFIABLE PROOF\nGENERATION\n\nEvents are canonicalized,\nhashed, signed, and wrapped\nwith verification metadata\nso operators can validate\nwhat happened.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.5,
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "AXCE8",
                  "name": "solutionCard3A",
                  "width": 400,
                  "height": 320,
                  "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                  "padding": 20,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "dzPTN",
                      "name": "solutionCard3TextA",
                      "fill": "#101419",
                      "content": "03  POLICY-GATED\nPERSISTENCE\n\nBefore records are accepted\ninto the ledger, policy rules\ncan reject stale, malformed,\nor risky flows so the trail\nstays cleaner.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.5,
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 15,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "SYUQE",
          "name": "pipelineSectionH",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "height": 980,
          "fill": "#0A0A0B",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 22,
          "padding": 72,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "GLcNw",
              "name": "pipelineTitleH",
              "fill": "#F7F8FA",
              "content": "The current Bridge Kernel operating flow",
              "fontFamily": "Manrope",
              "fontSize": 56,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Cf3Eq",
              "name": "pipelineBodyH",
              "fill": "#96A0AD",
              "content": "JouleBridge is strongest when the path from source event\nto reviewable evidence is clear. The current runtime baseline\ncan be understood as a three-step flow rather than a cluster\nof raw terminals.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Manrope",
              "fontSize": 18,
              "fontWeight": "500"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "whXZc",
              "name": "pipelineCardsB",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 520,
              "gap": 20,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "dJQFy",
                  "name": "pipelineCard1B",
                  "width": 396,
                  "height": 520,
                  "fill": "#12161D",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 12,
                  "padding": 20,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "zBQuW",
                      "name": "pipelineCard1TitleB",
                      "fill": "#4DD7C8",
                      "content": "STEP 01  CAPTURE",
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "BfaBX",
                      "name": "pipelineCard1BodyB",
                      "fill": "#F7F8FA",
                      "content": "Input\nWebhook, file ingest, scanner input, or baseline adapters\n\nWhat happens\nNormalize records into a deterministic internal shape.\n\nOutput\nStable event object ready for proofing.",
                      "fontFamily": "Manrope",
                      "fontSize": 18,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "lx7IE",
                  "name": "pipelineCard2B",
                  "width": 396,
                  "height": 520,
                  "fill": "#12161D",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 12,
                  "padding": 20,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "m1qqM",
                      "name": "pipelineCard2TitleB",
                      "fill": "#4DD7C8",
                      "content": "STEP 02  PROVE",
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "79UY5",
                      "name": "pipelineCard2BodyB",
                      "fill": "#F7F8FA",
                      "content": "Input\nCanonical event payload plus signing identity\n\nWhat happens\nHash, sign with Ed25519, attach verification metadata.\n\nOutput\nProof envelope ready for review.",
                      "fontFamily": "Manrope",
                      "fontSize": 18,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "u3LpM",
                  "name": "pipelineCard3B",
                  "width": 396,
                  "height": 520,
                  "fill": "#12161D",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 12,
                  "padding": 20,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "rwBOP",
                      "name": "pipelineCard3TitleB",
                      "fill": "#4DD7C8",
                      "content": "STEP 03  GOVERN",
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "lJ3af",
                      "name": "pipelineCard3BodyB",
                      "fill": "#F7F8FA",
                      "content": "Input\nProof-backed event plus active policy bundle\n\nWhat happens\nRun policy checks before persistence.\n\nOutput\nVerified records move forward, exceptions hold for review.",
                      "fontFamily": "Manrope",
                      "fontSize": 18,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "9lKCR",
          "name": "platformSectionH",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "height": 1040,
          "fill": "#EEF2F6",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 22,
          "padding": 72,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "9VJ4A",
              "name": "platformTitleH",
              "fill": "#101419",
              "content": "Built to make high-trust telemetry\noperationally usable.",
              "fontFamily": "Manrope",
              "fontSize": 56,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "QPU3X",
              "name": "platformBodyH",
              "fill": "#556273",
              "content": "Bridge Kernel is designed to run where the data is born, so verification starts at the operational edge instead of being bolted on later.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Manrope",
              "fontSize": 18,
              "fontWeight": "500"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "W02T7",
              "name": "platformGridB",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 520,
              "gap": 24,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "t9wAS",
                  "name": "platformLeftB",
                  "width": 760,
                  "height": 420,
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 16,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "DW7j7",
                      "name": "platformFeaturesB",
                      "fill": "#101419",
                      "content": "Edge-first runtime\nBridge Kernel is designed to run where the data is born.\n\nAdapter-based ingestion\nThe current implementation already supports adapter-driven capture flows.\n\nDeterministic proof pipeline\nRecords are canonicalized, hashed, signed, and paired with verification metadata.\n\nReplay-aware controls\nReplay windows, deduplication, and policy controls help filter bad flows.\n\nLedger and sync baseline\nLocal persistence and controlled sync create a foundation for higher-trust movement.\n\nRoadmap-driven hardening\nCloud control, dashboards, advanced protocol support, and broader commercial surfaces are being layered around the runtime core.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.45,
                      "fontFamily": "Manrope",
                      "fontSize": 22,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "Rw7cv",
                  "name": "platformRightB",
                  "width": 500,
                  "height": 460,
